    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10556: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 14, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>333. Your 881, October 12, 5, p.m. The view of the Department that “foreign
                    nations should stand so far as possible aloof from the internal dissensions in
                    China” is unchanged (see Department’s telegram May 17 [<hi rend="italic"
                    >18</hi>], 5 p.m., 1922).<note n="2" xml:id="d472fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1922v01#pg_705">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1922, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 705</ref>.</note> At your discretion you
                    may advise American shipping companies that the degree of protection this
                    Government can afford them in their normal activities will be adversely affected
                    to the extent that they allow themselves to become involved in Chinese military
                    operations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
